    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">King Ferdinand I to Miklós Oláh (Fronleiten, 15 November
                    1551)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">1. He is sending him Giovanni Battista Castaldo’s letter
                            of 7 November, from which he will learn that their army attacked Lipova
                            on 4 November and occupied it, and they slayed down 2,000 of the 3,000
                            Turks Sokollu Mehmed Pasha had left to defend it, the rest retreated to
                            the castle of Lipova with the rest of the sanjaks; there is great hope
                            for destroying all of the Pasha’s army. 2. So now things may turn to the
                            glory of not only Hungary but that of all of Christian Europe. He is
                            trying to keep Oláh updated, who should inform Ferenc Újlaki, Pál
                            Bornemissza, and the rest of the Hungarian councillors.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Ferdinandus etc. Reverendissime Devote Fidelis nobis Dilecte!</p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">[1.] Transmittimus Devotioni Tuae exemplum litterarum, quas
                    consiliarius noster et serenissimi principis domini
                        <persName>Maximiliani</persName> regis Bohemiae etc. filii nostri carissimi
                    bellicus locumtenens, <persName>Iohannes Baptesta Castaldus</persName><note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.1">Giovanni Battista Castaldo.</note> ex castris
                    ad <placeName>Lippam</placeName> positis die septima praesentis mensis Novembris
                    ad nos dedit,<note type="critic" xml:id="note.2">We only know a letter from 9
                        November, 1551, see ÖStA HHStA UA AA Fasc. 60. Konv. C. 1551. XI. fol.
                        22–23.</note> ex quibus Devotio Tua intelliget, quod ex singulari <add
                        corresp="scriba" type="insert">quadam</add> gratia <del corresp="scriba">qua
                        nos</del><del corresp="scriba">omnipotens</del><add corresp="scriba"
                        type="corr">omnipotentis</add> ac <del corresp="scriba">aeternus</del><add
                        corresp="scriba" type="corr">aeterni</add><del corresp="scriba">Deus
                        prosequetur</del><add corresp="scriba" type="corr">Dei</add> exercitus
                    noster ipsam civitatem <placeName>Lippam</placeName><del corresp="scriba"
                        >fortiter</del> die 4. praesentis <del corresp="scriba">firmiter
                        for</del><add corresp="scriba" type="corr">mensis</add> tormentis bellicis
                    conquassatam fortiter ingressus coeperit, ibidemque ex tribus millibus Turcarum
                    selectorum ex universo exercitu <del corresp="scriba">Turcico
                        Beglerbegi</del><add corresp="scriba" type="corr">et
                            <persName>Beglergbego</persName>,<note type="critic" xml:id="note.3"
                            >Sokollu Mehmed Pasha.</note> quos ad praesidium ac custodiam civitatis
                        reliquerat, quos ad praesidium ac custodiam civitatis reliquerat</add>,
                    circiter duo millia trucidaverunt, <del corresp="scriba">reliquis</del><add
                        corresp="scriba" type="corr">reliquos</add> vero <add corresp="scriba"
                        type="insert">Turcos</add> cum suo <persName>sanziacko</persName> in arcem,
                    quae ibi est, sese recepisset <del corresp="scriba"><add corresp="scriba"
                            type="insert">sesecumque</add></del>, magnamque <del corresp="scriba"
                        >tamen</del> esse spem non solum hos, qui in arcem illam profugerunt, verum
                    reliquum etiam <add corresp="scriba" type="insert">totum</add> ipsius
                        <persName>Baglerbegi</persName> exercitum <del corresp="scriba">Deo</del>
                    eodem Deo optimo maximo propitio funditus <add corresp="scriba" type="insert"
                        >brevi admodum tempore</add> oppressum iri. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">[2.] Quae cum ita se habeant, <add corresp="scriba" type="insert">et
                        non modo ad nostram regnique nostri Hungariae totiusque reipublicae
                        Christianiae salutem et incrementum, sed autem ad gloriam ac laudem Dei
                        pertinere videantur</add>. Nos sane Devotionem Tuam pro nostra in eandem
                    clementia celare minime potuimus, ut non solum Devotio Tua de istis rebus
                    certior <del corresp="scriba">reddatur</del> redducatur, sed eadem <add
                        corresp="scriba" type="insert">per Devotionem Tuam</add> locumtenenti quoque
                    nostro regni nostri Hungariae <del corresp="scriba"
                        >episcopo</del><persName>Iauriensi</persName><note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.4">Ferenc Újlaki.</note> ac
                        <persName>Vesprimiensi</persName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.5">Pál
                        Bornemissza.</note> episcopis ceterisque consiliariis nostris Hungaricis
                        <add corresp="scriba" type="insert">facta et illis litterarum illarum
                        copia</add> communicarentur. Quare Devotio Tua una cum illis eidem <add
                        corresp="scriba" type="insert">etiam</add> omnipotenti Domino, cuius
                    auspiciis res haec est feliciter conscripta<note type="critic" xml:id="note.6"
                        >Uncertain reading.</note> dignas gratias agere <del corresp="scriba"
                        >debebant</del> priumquam laudis sacrificium celebrare debebit, quo is
                    huiusmodi gratiarum actione et laudibus clementer attentis<milestone unit="pb"
                    />posthac etiam nobis <del corresp="scriba">eandem gratiam suam</del> regnisque
                        <del corresp="scriba">nostris Hungariae</del> ac dominiciis nostris et
                    universae reipublicae Christianae <del corresp="scriba">adesse</del> propitius
                    adesse <add corresp="scriba" type="insert">coeptumque opus ad felicem finem
                        suique nominis sempiternam gloriam deducere</add> non dedigneretur, prout
                    Devotionem Tuam facturam esse <del corresp="scriba">minimi</del><add
                        corresp="scriba" type="corr">minime</add> dubitamus. <del corresp="scriba"
                        >Et ista sancta</del></p>
                <p xml:id="p.4">Datum in <placeName>Fronleik</placeName> die <del corresp="scriba"
                        >16</del><add corresp="scriba" type="corr">15</add>. Novembris 1551.</p>
            </div>
            <div style="handwritten" type="verso" xml:id="d.2">
                <head>Probably on the outer side:</head>
                <p xml:id="p.5">Episcopo Agriensi.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
